The People of the State of New York, Respondent, v James Cassano, Appellant. [727 NYS2d 620]

—Application by the appellant for a writ of error coram nobis to vacate, on the ground of ineffective assistance of appellate counsel, a decision and order of this Court dated January 29, 2001 (People v Cassano, 279 AD2d 636), affirming a judgment of the Supreme Court, Kings County, rendered March 2, 1999.

Ordered that the application is denied.

The appellant has failed to establish that he was denied the effective assistance of appellate counsel (see, Jones v Barnes, 463 US 745). Ritter, J. P., Altman, H. Miller and Schmidt, JJ., concur.
